<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="111" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,151,357]" pageId="8" pageNumber="111">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,223,248]" pageId="8" pageNumber="111">Etymology.</emphasis>
The species name 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Blank &amp; Kramp &amp; Shinohara" authorityYear="2017" box="[546,605,224,248]" class="Insecta" family="Xyelidae" genus="Xyela" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="111" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fusca">
<emphasis box="[546,605,224,248]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="111">fusca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, an adjective, was chosen to refer to the predominately infuscate head and mesonotum.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
